The Quebec Radio Moderator Stéphane Dupont suffered a partial setback in front of the Canadian Supervisory Board for Broadcasting Standards (CCNR) because of his controversial statements about social welfare and Haitians, as well as because of his speech about radio.
The CCNR believes that while M. Dupont and his CHOI 98.1 FM team have the right to express their opinions, certain statements "would have contained impeccable information on social welfare and unjustified negative representations of the Haitians, as well as such a crude speech that is not appropriate to the broadcasts broadcast during the day."
